    <text id="B1119T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How requests that the Bureau pay the travelling expenses for several destitute
                    blacks who wish to join family members elsewhere. The letter's wrapper details
                    the channels through which the request passed.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="section" id="wrapper">
                <p><abbr expan="Headquarters">Hd Qrs</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr>, Bureau <abbr
                        expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. and A.L.</abbr>, 19
                    September 1865<lb/><hi rend="underline">Approved</hi>, and respectfully
                    forwarded to <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="Major General">Maj. Genl</abbr>
                        O.O. Howard</hi>, Commissioner<lb/>(signed) O. Brown, <abbr expan="Colonel"
                        >Col.</abbr> and <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr></p>
                <p>War Department, Bureau Refugees, Freedmen &amp;c, Washington, <abbr
                        expan="September">Sept.</abbr> 21<hi rend="super">st</hi>
                    1865<lb/>Respectfully returned to Colonel Brown, <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> &amp;c to know whether
                    these people are dependent on the Bureau for support.<lb/>By order of <abbr
                        expan="Major General">Maj. Genl</abbr> Howard,
                        Commissioner<lb/>(signed)<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Adjutant">Asst. Adjt.
                        General</abbr></p>
                <p>Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                    A.L.</abbr>, Richmond, <abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 23/65<lb/><abbr
                        expan="Respectfully">Respy</abbr> Returned: attention invited to previous
                        <orig reg="endorsement ">indorsement</orig>by order <abbr expan="Colonel"
                        >Col.</abbr> O. Brown, (signed)H.B. Scott, <del rend="none" hand="h1"/><abbr
                        expan="General">Genl</abbr></p>
                <p><abbr expan="Headquarters">HdQrs</abbr> Sixth <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>, Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 29<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                    '65<lb/>Respectfully returned to <abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> Brown with
                    the information that these people are not dependent on this Bureau for
                    support<lb/>(signed)W. Storer How, <abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp;c,
                        <abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt.</abbr> Sixth <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees Freedmen &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned">A.</abbr>
                    Lands<lb/><abbr expan="Headquarters">H<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                        Quarters</abbr> Sixth District <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr><lb/>Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-09-16"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 16<hi
                                rend="super">th</hi> 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to apply for transportation for the following named persons, to
                    the places and for the reasons set opposite their names.</p>

                <p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Violet Ward, 2 children - colored</cell>
                            <cell>to Holmes <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                                <abbr expan="Mississippi">Miss.</abbr></cell>
                            <cell>Her husband &amp; one child, live in <abbr expan="Mississippi"
                                    >Miss.</abbr> one child here &amp; one in Richmond</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Catherine Johnson, one child - Colored</cell>
                            <cell>to Richmond, Va</cell>
                            <cell>She has five children in Richmond</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Mahala Montgomery &amp; four children - Colored</cell>
                            <cell>to Clear Spring - 11 miles from Hagarstown <abbr expan="Maryland"
                                    >Md.</abbr></cell>
                            <cell>She is unable to support herself here, &amp; has relations
                                there who will support her.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Nancy <unclear>Ellet</unclear> &amp; 2 children - <abbr
                                    expan="Colored">Cold</abbr></cell>
                            <cell>To Fauquier <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                                <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></cell>
                            <cell>has 4 children there &amp; former owner</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>

                <p>These persons are all destitute, unable to pay their traveling expenses
                    themselves.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, Colonel <lb/>Very Respectfully,<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient"
                            >Obed</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>W. Storer How <abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Quartermaster">A.Q.M.</abbr><lb/><abbr
                            expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> 6th <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
